    "actions_taken": [
      "Driller disengaged drawworks clutch stopping upward movement",
      "Traveling block slacked off approximately 10 feet",
      "Brake locked down and incident reported",
      "Crown block inspected for damage",
      "Well operations suspended until inspectors could check condition of block, wire rope, and crown",
      "Root Cause Investigation conducted by contractor and operator"
    ],
    "summary": "On July 8, 2024, while pulling out of the hole with drill pipe on the jack-up rig Enterprise 205, the traveling block struck the crown saver assembly with approximately 117,000 lbs overpull, resulting in $11,210 in damages. The driller lost situational awareness while checking the pipe tally, and the crown-o-matic (COM) failed to trip when contacted by the drill line because the barrel wasn't set properly. Contributing factors included inadequate hazard analysis in the JSA, lack of rig-specific procedures for checking the COM, and failure of floorhand to count tool joints during the operation.",
